{title: The Barn Dance}
{artist: Tom T. Hall}
{composer: unknown}

I [C]peeked through the big ole crack in the door
And [F]what do you think I [C]saw
The animals havin' a barn dance
[G7]Right in the horse's [C]stall
And there was chicken doin' chicken reel
And the [F]muskrat rambled [C]on
The ol' cow did a cow-cow boogie
And the [D7]rooster crowed the [G7]song
A [C]mouse came out of his hidin' place
And he [F]danced on one [C]leg
The ol' hen got so tickled
That she [G7]almost laid an [C]egg
They were all dressed up for the barn dance
It [F]made me want to [C]laugh
The rabbit wore the big bowtie
And the [D7]pig was a lookin' in the [G7]lookin' glass
And the [C]goose danced with the gander
Till an [F]old dog butted [C]in
